The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Hyderabad, Oct. 5: A local court today issued non-bailable warrants against Helmut Schuster, former India representative of Volksawagen, and Gayatri Rai, sister of Jagdish Alagar Raja, the kingpin of Vashisht Wahan Co, the Indian arm of Volkswagen. On a plea by the CBI, metropolitan magistrate K Surya Rao issued the warrants against the two for allegedly cheating the Andhra government of Rs 11.76 crore. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 5: The department of public enterprises has decided to appoint non-functional directors on PSU boards on the basis of the March 2004 guidelines, which states senior bureaucrats ? having served not less than 10 years as joint secretary ? or university professors, technocrats, institute heads and corporate leaders can be appointed as independent directors.

 Mumbai, Oct. 5: The government is planning to increase the financial autonomy of ports to Rs 500 crore from Rs 100 crore, said shipping minister T.R. Baalu.

 Mumbai, Oct. 5: Jubilant Organosys has acquired US-based Target Research Associates, a full-service clinical research firm, for $33.5 million in an all-cash deal.

 New Delhi, Oct. 5: Steel Authority (SAIL) has moved the company law board for actual transfer of assets belonging to Iisco.




